    dc:creator "Peck, Stewart B.; Cook, Joyce" ;
    dc:date "2009" ;
    dc:title "Review of the Sogdini of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Leiodidae: Leiodinae) with descriptions of fourteen new species and three new genera" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310886>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310890>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310892> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310886>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–4. Sogdini, habitus photos. 1. Triarthron lecontei, total length 3.4 mm. 2. Hydnobius autumnalis, total length 3.0 mm. 3. Stereus arenarius, total length 3.4 mm. 4. Sogda obtusa, total length 3.4 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5310886/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310890>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8–13. Triarthron lecontei. 8. Right antenna, dorsal view. 9. Mandibles, dorsal view. 10. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 11. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 12. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 13. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 11, 13), 0.5 mm (Figs. 8, 9, 12), 0.75 mm (Fig. 10)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5310890/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310892>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Known North American localities of Triarthron lecontei (black dots). In this and all following maps, small white circles indicate major cities." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5310892/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

